block content
  #banner.container
    .rays   
    .text
      .intro A robust and extendable web framework for Node.js
      .get-started
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/guide.html") Guide
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/examples/index.html") Examples
        a.btn.btn-primary(href="/api/index.html") API
      .version v#{version}
      .meta.hidden-xs
        div
          iframe(src="http://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=waigo&repo=waigo&type=watch&size=small&count=true", allowtransparency="true", frameborder="0", scrolling="0", width="100", height="20")
        div
          <a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button">Tweet</a>
          <script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?'http':'https';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+'://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js';fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document, 'script', 'twitter-wjs');</script>

  section#details1
    .intro.row
      .col-md-6.col-md-offset-3.col-xs-12
        h2 What is Waigo?
        :markdown
          Waigo is a low-level framework for building scalable web applications in Node.js. Waigo combines **es6 generators**
          with a **flexible module loading** mechanism and **configurable architecture** to enable you to build the application 
          you need, without getting in your way.
    .features.row
      .col-md-4
        h3 Easy
        ul
          li Built on <a href="http://koajs.com" target="_blank">Koa/Express</a> middleware architecture.
          li <a href="/guide.html#command-line">Command-line</a> client to automate tasks.
      .col-md-4
        h3 Elegant
        ul
          li No more callback hell. Generators and promises are in.
          li <a href="/api">Minimal core</a> framework, with no unneeded cruft.
      .col-md-4
        h3 Extendable
        ul
          li Easily <a href="/guide.html#extend-and-override">override</a> framework behaviour.
          li Create and share customizations as <a href="/guide.html#plugins">plugins</a>.

  section#details2
    h2 Quick start
    .row
      .col-md-6
        pre
          code.language-bash
            $ npm install -g waigo
            $ waigo init
            $ ./start-app.js
      .col-md-6
        :markdown 
          If you visit `http://localhost:3000` in your browser you should see 
          some welcome text.

          You can now start adding controllers and models and develop your 
          application.


  section#sublinks
    .row
      .col-md-3
        h4
          a(href="/guide.html") Guide &raquo;
        p An in-depth introduction to Waigo and how to use it.
      .col-md-3
        h4
          a(href="/examples") Examples &raquo;
        p Fully documented examples of using Waigo in different ways. 
      .col-md-3
        h4
          a(href="/api") API docs &raquo;
        p Detailed API documentation for every file in the core framework.
      .col-md-3
        h4
          a(href="https://github.com/waigo/waigo/issues") Github &raquo;
        p Bugs, features and other community discussion items.
